Title: Note on Holographic RG Flow in String Cosmology
Authors: Miao Li and Feng-Li Lin
Comments: 15 pages, no figure; v3. references added, final to CQG
Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 19 (2002) 3281-3292
\\
  We propose a new holographic C-function for the accelerating universe defined
in the stringy frame motivated mainly by the fact that the number of degrees of
freedom should be infinite for a physical system of infinite size. This is the
generalization of Strominger's recent proposal of the holographic C-function to
the asymptotically non-de Sitter universe. We find that the corresponding
C-theorem holds true if the universe accelerates toward the weak coupling
regime driven by the exponential dilaton potential. It also holds in other
simple cases.
